Comment 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E5FFFB2FEE9FEB7D88EFE87" baseAuthorityName="KRAATZ" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[336,499,332,353]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Astenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indicus">
<emphasis id="B90819228E5FFFB2FEE9FEB7D88EFE87" box="[336,499,332,353]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">Astenus indicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously known from the Afrotropical region, Sicily, 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E5FFFB2FF49FE92D852FE98" box="[240,303,361,382]" name="Egypt" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, the East Palaearctic, and the Australian region (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E5FFFB2FCF0FE92DA8DFE99" author="SMETANA A" box="[841,1008,361,383]" pageId="4" pageNumber="145" pagination="505 - 698" refId="ref7869" refString="SMETANA A. (2004): Staphylinidae, subfamilies Omaliinae - Dasycerinae, Phloeocharinae - Apaticinae, Piestinae - Staphylininae, pp. 237 - 272, 329 - 495, 505 - 698. - In: LOBL I. &amp; A. SMETANA (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. II. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphylinoidea. - Stenstrup, Apollo Books: 942 pp." type="book chapter" year="2004">SMETANA 2004</bibRefCitation>
). The above specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E5FFFB2FE35FE7DDB6CFE7A" box="[396,529,390,412]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E5FFFB2FDFAFE7DDBFDFE7A" box="[579,640,390,412]" name="Oman" pageId="4" pageNumber="145">Oman</collectingCountry>
represent new country records.
</paragraph>
